```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return replace(lowercase(strip(col)), [" ", "-"] => "_")
end
```

This function first strips any leading or trailing whitespaces using `strip`, then lowercases the string with `lowercase`, and finally replaces both spaces and hyphens with underscores using `replace`. The result is a column name that is all lowercase with underscores instead of spaces or hyphens.
